title: Kingdoms and Strongholds of the Crusaders (Architecure History)
description:
Kingdoms and Strongholds of the Crusaders
The Bobbs-Merrill Company | 1971 | 0500250294 | English | 282 pages | PDF | 52 MB

In the grand panorama of history, the states established in the eastern Mediterranean by the crusaders appear to have been an ephemeral medieval side-issue.
Yet the impact of these states on their time, and the mark they have left on history, are out of all proportion to the number of people involved
